<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="501" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d501">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.62114A/4–1345: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-16T15:00:00-04:00">April 16,
                                    1945—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1501. According to further information received (see Bern’s 2168, April
                            13 repeated to Paris for <hi rend="smallcaps">Widewing</hi> B) last two
                            words “against Germany” in first paragraph of Department’s 1486 April
                            14, should be deleted. Inform French authorities of this correction and
                            proceed in accordance with previous instructions without extending time
                            of three day period allowed for reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>